Former Manchester United boss, Jose Mourinho could reportedly be back to the Premier League as Arsenal manager, according to The Times. The former Chelsea manager’s last job was in Manchester United where he was sacked last November. The Portuguese, however, could return to the Premier League as several reports are linking him to Arsenal. The 56-year-old was seen at the Gunners Europa League match against Vitoria SC
Arsenal are having a difficult start to the Premier League this season as they are currently 5th in the table. The newspaper reports that manager Unai Emery could be sacked if the North London club don’t make the Champions League next season. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.